HEADWORD: Hermodactyl
<hw>Her`mo*dac"tyl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>hermodactylus</ets>, lit., Hermes' finger; fr. Gr. <?/ Hermes + <?/
finger.]</ety> <fld>(med.)</fld> <def>A heart-shaped bulbous root, about
the size of a finger, brought from Turkey, formerly used as a
cathartic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

